OL,3,CWhat is the role of the King on
OL,4,Cresults day?
OL,6,FBut one of the King's remaining
OL,7,Fprerogative powers (exercised by the
OL,8,FMonarch acting alone) is his role in
OL,9,Fappointing a prime minister.
OL,11,FThe Monarch's job is to ask the leader
OL,12,Fof the largest party in the House of
OL,13,FCommons, now Sir Keir Starmer, if he
OL,14,Fcan command the confidence of the
OL,15,FHouse. In other words, does he have a
OL,16,Fworking majority of MPs with which he
OL,17,Fcan form a stable government?
